.TH LIVE-BOOT-REFRESH 1 "June 2026" "mx-remaster" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
live-boot-refresh \- refresh live USB boot labels and menu titles
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B live-boot-refresh
.RI [ options "] [" mount-point ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Update the visible release name on a live USB tree.
The script rewrites the bootloader label metadata and refreshes menu titles in
.BR GRUB ,
isolinux, and syslinux configuration files when they are present.
.PP
If
.I mount-point
is omitted, the live boot device is located automatically by its boot UUID and
mounted read-write.  When the device is not present \(em for example after
booting with
.B toram
and ejecting the media \(em you are prompted to plug it back in and try again.
Auto-detection requires root and reads the live boot configuration, so it only
works on a running live system; pass an explicit
.I mount-point
otherwise.
.PP
The chosen tree must contain
.B antiX/
and
.B boot/
directories (an
.B EFI/
directory is used when present).

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -h , " --help"
Show help.
.TP
.BR -n , " --dry-run"
Show what would be changed without modifying files.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I linuxfs.ver
Source of the new release/title string.
.TP
.I bootloader-data
Boot metadata file whose
.B FULL_DISTRO_NAME
entry is updated.
.TP
.I grub.cfg
GRUB menu file whose release labels are updated in place.
.TP
.I isolinux.cfg
Menu title file whose release label is updated in place.
.TP
.I syslinux.cfg
Syslinux menu title file whose release label is updated in place.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR live-remaster (1),
.BR live-grubsave (1),
.BR live-setup (1)
.SH AUTHOR
mx-remaster maintainers
